<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/33–35.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">French
                                    Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August 13,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 429.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your note of the 7th instant, transmitting, by
                                instruction from his excellency the <pb facs="1043" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/> minister of foreign affairs, a note
                                acquainting this Government with the measures that have been adopted
                                and were deemed indispensable to insure the restoration of order and
                                safety in Morocco in consequence of the unforeseen outbreak at
                                Casablanca.</p>
                            <p>The note verbale, also transmitted by you with the above, is intended
                                to bring the particulars of these events to the department’s
                                knowledge.</p>
                            <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A.
                                Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>